<Base
  title="How We Rate Products — Our Methodology | The Life Insider"
  description="Exactly how The Life Insider's Insider Score works: verified customer review data, review volume weighting, value analysis, and brand reliability — explained in plain English."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <div class="kicker">Our Methodology</div>
      <h1>How We Rate Products</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <p class="lede">
        Every product we feature receives an <strong>Insider Score out of
        10</strong>. This page explains exactly where that number comes from —
        because a rating you can't verify is just an opinion.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>We hold every ranking to an exceedingly high standard of
        evidence, so you can have full confidence in our recommendations.</strong>
        We'd rather feature fewer products and be right than list everything and
        be useless.
      </p>

      <h2>The Insider Score: what goes into it</h2>
      <p>Our score is built from four weighted inputs:</p>

      <h3>1. Verified customer ratings (the foundation — 50%)</h3>
      <p>
        We start with what real, verified buyers report — the aggregate
        customer rating a product has earned at major retailers, normalized to
        a 10-point scale. A product rated 4.6 out of 5 stars by verified
        purchasers starts from a 9.2 baseline. We don't invent this number,
        and we don't inflate it: it reflects the experience of the people who
        actually bought and used the product.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Review volume and consistency (20%)</h3>
      <p>
        A 4.8-star product with 40 reviews is less proven than a 4.6-star
        product with 12,000. We weight scores by the volume of reviews behind
        them and check consistency over time — products whose recent reviews
        trend sharply below their historical average are flagged or excluded.
      </p>

      <h3>3. Value for money (15%)</h3>
      <p>
        We compare each product's price against its closest competitors,
        factoring in current discounts, cost per use where relevant, and what
        you get for the money (materials, warranty length, included extras).
      </p>

      <h3>4. Brand reliability and buyer protection (15%)</h3>
      <p>
        Returns windows, warranty terms, shipping speed, and the brand's track
        record of standing behind its products. A great product from a company
        that won't take it back if something goes wrong is not a great buy.
      </p>

      <h2>What our badges mean</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Best Overall / Editor's Choice</strong> — the highest combined Insider Score in the category.</li>
        <li><strong>Best Value</strong> — the strongest score relative to price.</li>
        <li><strong>Deal badges</strong> — a genuine, currently-running discount from the retailer or brand. We do not display expired or fabricated offers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we don't do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>We don't fabricate test results or claim laboratory testing we haven't performed. Where our team has hands-on experience with a product, we say so explicitly; otherwise, our analysis is data-driven.</li>
        <li>We don't display fake review counts or invented user ratings. Review figures shown on our pages reflect actual retailer data at the time of our last update.</li>
        <li>We don't accept payment to change a product's score. Compensation can influence <em>which categories and products we choose to feature</em> and their placement — never the underlying score. See our <a href="/advertising-disclosure/">Advertising Disclosure</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we make money</h2>
      <p>
        When you buy through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate
        commission from the retailer or brand — at no extra cost to you. This
        is how we fund our research. It's also why we're transparent about it:
        our long-term business depends on you trusting our recommendations
        enough to come back. Full details are in our
        <a href="/advertising-disclosure/">Advertising Disclosure</a> and
        <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">Affiliate Disclosure</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Updates and corrections</h2>
      <p>
        Rankings are reviewed and refreshed regularly as prices, availability,
        and review data change. Every review page displays its last-updated
        date. If you believe any information on our site is inaccurate, please
        <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> and we'll investigate promptly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
